2.title: The Druggie
2.plot: When Deb unwittingly eats some shrooms, she flashes back into some memories she'd rather forget. Luckily, Min is there to hold Deb's hand. But it turns out that Min might need some handholding of her own.

3.title: Mother
3.plot: As Min is faced with a difficult decision, Deb tries to engage Min in her newfound love of meditation; however, Min's painful childhood memories seem to win the day. Is there anything Deb can do to help her friend?

4.title: No More Marilyn Monroe
4.plot: With the deep struggles of women in Hollywood and our allies, we female filmmakers, writers, actors and creatives are now bravely coming together to make our voices heard and to claim our creative rights. We, Deb and Min, and the Wingin' It team are proud to be a part of this movement.

5.title: Desperately Seeking Baby
5.plot: Deb goes wild with trying to have a baby. Min saves the day for once.

imdb.plot outline: Written and produced by Minerva Vier and Debbie Jaffe, Wingin' It is a dark comedy about the misadventures of two alienated and desperate women on the brink of nervous breakdowns. Deb is a neurotic socialite hitting the skids. She could have been one of the stars of The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills if only her ex-fiancee did not dump her right before their perfect wedding. Min is an emotional mess of an artist whose suicidal tendencies have flared up since her ex-boyfriend, a Charlie Manson wannabe, left her for his doped-up groupies. Bonding over their misery, Deb and Min find a mutual shoulder to cry on and embark on a roller-coaster adventure together in their quest to heal their broken hearts.
